# Design Depth: Borders-Only Strategy

## Core Rule
In dark mode and EVA mode, **depth is communicated exclusively through borders** — not shadows, not blur, not glow.

## What Is FORBIDDEN in dark/EVA mode

```ts
// ❌ NEVER: glassmorphism
backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
-webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px);

// ❌ NEVER: neumorphism
box-shadow: inset 4px 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.3), -4px -4px 10px rgba(255,255,255,0.05);

// ❌ NEVER: glow shadows on cards
box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.4);

// ❌ NEVER: hardcoded rgba borders without depth token
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);  // use depth token instead
```

## What Is REQUIRED in dark/EVA mode

```ts
// ✅ ALWAYS: use depth tokens for borders
border: 1px solid ${props => props.theme.depth?.cardBorder ?? props.theme.colors.border};

// ✅ ALWAYS: use depth token for hover border
&:hover {
  border-color: ${props => props.theme.depth?.cardBorderHover ?? props.theme.colors.primary[500]};
}

// ✅ ALWAYS: subtle background if needed
background: ${props => props.theme.depth?.cardBackground ?? 'transparent'};
```

## Depth Token Reference

| Token | Dark value | EVA value | Use case |
|-------|-----------|-----------|----------|
| `depth.cardBorder` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.06)` | `rgba(139,92,246,0.12)` | Card resting border |
| `depth.cardBorderHover` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.14)` | `rgba(139,92,246,0.25)` | Card hover border |
| `depth.cardBorderFocus` | `rgba(59,130,246,0.5)` | `rgba(139,92,246,0.5)` | Focused element border |
| `depth.dividerBorder` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.04)` | `rgba(139,92,246,0.06)` | Section dividers |
| `depth.emphasisBorder` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.10)` | `rgba(139,92,246,0.18)` | Important elements |
| `depth.modalShadow` | `0 25px 50px -12px rgba(0,0,0,0.7)` | `0 25px 50px -12px rgba(88,28,135,0.6)` | Modals/overlays only |
| `depth.floatBorder` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.12)` | `rgba(139,92,246,0.20)` | Floating elements |
| `depth.cardBackground` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.02)` | `rgba(139,92,246,0.03)` | Subtle card fill |

## Exceptions (Allowed blur)

These UI patterns are semantically overlay elements — blur is appropriate:
- `Modal` / `Dialog` overlays
- `Tooltip` popups
- `LoadingSpinner` backdrop
- `ConfirmationDialog`

## Elevation Through Borders (The Rule)

```
Level 0 (page bg)    → no border
Level 1 (card)       → depth.cardBorder (0.06 opacity)
Level 2 (hover card) → depth.cardBorderHover (0.14 opacity)
Level 3 (focus)      → depth.cardBorderFocus (0.5 opacity, colored)
Level 4 (modal)      → depth.modalShadow (shadow allowed for true overlays)
```

Higher opacity = higher elevation. Simple. Consistent. Terminal aesthetic.
